    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# VECTOR INDEXING\n\n- Makes KB updates idempotent before writing fresh vectors.\n- Pinecone insert does not automatically replace old file chunks, so this section deletes stale vectors first.\n- Namespace is set upstream in `Prepare Chunk Metadata` and read by Pinecone as `={{ $json.namespace || 'SpaceKonceptRental_kb' }}`.\n\n## Pinecone cleanup subflow:\n\n- **Resolve Pinecone Index Host**: Gets the live Pinecone host for `pinecone_index_name`.\n- **Prepare Pinecone Delete Request**: Builds a `/vectors/delete` request for the current `source_file_id` or `source_file_name`.\n- **Delete Existing Pinecone File Chunks**: Removes old chunks for that file from the namespace. A first-run `Namespace not found` response is allowed because there are no old vectors yet.\n- **Restore Pinecone Ingestion Context**: Validates the delete result, throws for unexpected Pinecone delete errors, then restores the original document item so embedding and insert can continue normally.\n\n## Required manual configuration:\n\n- **Prepare Chunk Metadata**\n  - `pinecone_index_name`: Keep this aligned with the Pinecone index used for vector storage.\n- **Insert Chunks into Pinecone**\n  - `pineconeIndex`: Set this to the same Pinecone index used for vector storage.",
        "height": 940,
        "width": 1384,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000903",
      "name": "Vector indexing group",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -80,
        -320
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# INGESTION LOG\n\n- Records ingestion status for review.\n- Groups Pinecone chunk outputs back into one log row per source file.\n- Appends every ingestion event as a new audit row; repeated file events must not overwrite earlier rows.\n- Keeps explicit column mappings in `Append KB Ingestion Log`; changing the Sheets operation in the UI can clear them.\n- Uses RAW sheet writes so file names stay literal while chunk counts remain numeric.\n- Sets the `file_name` column hyperlink display to plain text after logging; `file_url` remains the clickable Drive URL.\n\n## Required manual configuration:\n\n- **Append KB Ingestion Log**\n  - `documentId.value`: Set this to the Google Sheets workbook used for ingestion logs.\n  - Sheet headers must include `file_url` and `event_type` if those columns are used.\n- **Disable File Name Hyperlinks**\n  - `url`: Keep the spreadsheet ID aligned with `Append KB Ingestion Log.documentId.value`.\n  - `range.sheetId` and column indexes: Keep these aligned with the `kb_ingestion` sheet and the `file_name` column.",
        "height": 940,
        "width": 820,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000904",
